{
  "texts": [
    "Present AI solutions lack real-time perception of user requirements, resulting in best-effort services.",
    "In response, 6G mobile networks must ensure low-latency and highreliability AI as a service.",
    "Therefore, in terms of architecture design, unified AI service quality evaluation metrics and an end-to-end guarantee mechanism must be designed for AI service quality.",
    "From high-cost postprocessing to low-cost preintervention.",
    "Currently, the effectiveness of network AI models can only be verified retrospectively, which creates a conflict between the probabilistic nature of AI and the reliability requirements of a network."
  ]
}